We uniformly analyzed 723 RNA-seq datasets in cattle as described in (http://cattlegeneatlas.roslin.ed.ac.uk/). To detect tissue/cell type specific genes, we computed a t-statistics of each gene in each of 91 tissue/cell types after correcting for known batch effects. We scaled the log2-transformed expression (i.e., log2FPKM) of genes to have a mean of zero and variance of one within each tissue and cell type.
\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
